g.text: ArthurRank3Convo4 begins.

g.title: j2420967462
g.text: So, how'd you wind up in Duviri in the first place?

g.title: j4270747467
g.text: That's... a really easy question with a really hard answer.

g.title: j1654364926
g.text: My other option was to lose my mind.

g.title: j4046047942
g.text: It's one of the best vacation spots.

g.title: j3187796158
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j3131762126
g.text: What?

g.title: j1828192037
g.text: I'm going to assume that's sarcasm.

g.title: j1074584780
g.text: Well, I'm listening.

g.title: j3209817377
g.text: It's a long story. A really long story.

g.title: j3779906564
g.text: I'd rather not get into this. [End.]

g.title: j2074074725
g.text: I cope through humor. I'm trying to deflect.

g.title: j2356745815
g.text: Yeah.

g.title: j1376144544
g.text: What was your first clue?

g.title: j544398843
g.text: Winding up in an imaginary-turned-real Void realm isn't like walking to the corner store.

g.title: j373521759
g.text: Good thing I'm sitting, then.

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.

g.title: j471872691
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j506171193
g.text: Look mate, if this is an uncomfortable topic, just say so.

g.title: j1279723249
g.text: It's not exactly a short story.

g.title: j2119944662
g.text: All right, all right... Buckle up.

g.title: j3418529660
g.text: Can we do this another time?

g.title: j356154204
g.text: This is a really uncomfortable topic for you.

g.title: j334590973
g.text: Sorry. You're right. I don't like talking about this.

g.title: j3770644984
g.text: I'm not being defensive.

g.title: j2415660199
g.text: If the emotions are what hurts, keep it to the facts. Let's start there.

g.title: j831544297
g.text: Sure. But I'm keeping you to that.

g.title: j1056016587
g.text: The thing about the past is, you get through it. But it can still hurt to talk about.

g.title: j2860364307
g.text: The other option is to cry constantly.

g.title: j1123067450
g.text: Can I ask why not?

g.title: j280388998
g.text: I didn't say you were being - never mind. We'll do this another time, then.

g.title: j1903818404
g.text: We'll cover the squishy bits another time. Deal?

g.title: j325721217
g.text: Boolean ArthurDuviri is now true.

g.title: j1653768147
g.text: Don't I know it.

g.title: j2986843144
g.text: Do you want to do this another time?

g.title: j9585548
g.text: It... it's messy.

g.title: j3642324132
g.text: Do you like talking about your screwed up past?

g.title: j2741161660
g.text: Easier said than done with Duviri, but...deal.

g.title: j2864620122
g.text: On second thought, no. [End.]

g.title: j2178737969
g.text: Now's fine.

g.title: j2787268712
g.text: Yeah. Later.

g.title: j694712363
g.text: Never's fine.

g.title: j1169883841
g.text: Messy how? Body count?

g.title: j1877357677
g.text: No. I don't.

g.title: j301827467
g.text: Boolean ArthurDuviri is now true.

g.title: j781709397
g.text: Good talk.

g.title: j1168059544
g.text: The void screws with everything. Timelines, reality, your head. Messy.

g.title: j3546945559
g.text: You're thinking like a soldier. Messy because of what it did to me.

g.title: j3847584464
g.text: But sometimes, turning these rocks over is how you learn to trust people.

g.title: j2546302550
g.text: We're all made up of the stories we're taught.

g.title: j114021748
g.text: The Man in the Wall is a lying, murdering bastard.

g.title: j1270016694
g.text: I'm starting to figure that out.

g.title: j3484577225
g.text: Gnnnhhh... Fine. But you owe me. A story for a story.

g.title: j1952057178
g.text: Another time, maybe?

g.title: j2345875072
g.text: Pass. [End.]

g.title: j484138061
g.text: Boolean ArthurDuviriInternal is now true.

g.title: j2297444299
g.text: Boolean ArthurDuviriExternal is now true.

g.title: j871881337
g.text: Deal.

g.title: j1967855668
g.text: All right.

g.title: j3623649850
g.text: How so?

g.title: j439142228
g.text: Hell of a way to start. I don't disagree, mind you. But hell of a way to start.

g.title: j2948718382
g.text: Boolean ArthurFamily is now true.

g.title: j1175142229
g.text: The stories we learn changes the world around us. In my case it's literal.

g.title: j3641167832
g.text: It's what it all comes back to in the end. That *thing* that haunts us.

g.title: j30431890
g.text: But I'm getting ahead of myself.

g.title: j459340895
g.text: The Void made our parents go insane. They were trying to eat us, Arthur. Then that *thing* showed up. Offered us powers.

g.title: j3668749475
g.text: Said the powers would save us all. But he didn't mean me.

g.title: j2326093794
g.text: I was left behind.

g.title: j1191367164
g.text: Two important things about the Void: One. It makes you go nuts.

g.title: j3031874383
g.text: Two: "Conceptual Embodiment." It takes things from your head and makes them real.

g.title: j3374369688
g.text: We had a book of stories written by Entrati's daughter about how not to go nuts in the void. And my mind snapped back to those.

g.title: j3869292512
g.text: So. Why did I go to Duviri?

g.title: j3300067689
g.text: Check boolean ArthurDuviriInternal

g.title: j1222235074
g.text: Because those stories said "come play with me. It's safe here. Let's go on adventures!"

g.title: j3300067689->j1222235074
g.text: true

g.title: j4258306565
g.text: Because the Man in the Wall wanted to play games. Because everybody has abandoned me my entire life.

g.title: j3300067689->j4258306565
g.text: false

g.title: j1350345033
g.text: The Void made a kingdom of sand from my memories and I grew up playing with storybook friends.

g.title: j1243225563
g.text: I went to Duviri because I didn't have a choice. Because the people there that the Void made? They were my friends, even if they weren't real.

g.title: j800840515
g.text: Until I outgrew them. And those friends became my nightmares.

g.title: j156737405
g.text: Until those friends became my nightmares.

g.title: j4033623414
g.text: And Dominus Thrax began executing me again, and again, and again...

g.title: j1829946186
g.text: And began executing me again, and again, and again...

g.title: j2164800104
g.text: So. Yeah. *That's* how I wound up in Duviri, Arthur.

g.title: j785144981
g.text: So. Yeah. *That's* how I wound up in Duviri, Arthur.

g.title: j1285432437
g.text: Because of the stories I was taught.

g.title: j2915727296
g.text: Because of the Man in the Wall. And Albrecht. And the Orokin. And all the stupid games everybody plays.

g.title: j549816165
g.text: I... feel like I just opened a serious can of worms.

g.title: j4187625612
g.text: Orowyrms, actually.

g.title: j211873199
g.text: You started it.

g.title: j3784158016
g.text: I warned you.

g.title: j1084604598
g.text: What?

g.title: j1721596888
g.text: That I did.

g.title: j801010156
g.text: That you did.

g.title: j3105394894
g.text: Never mind.

g.title: j3986826230
g.text: +15 Chemistry

g.title: j2959314246
g.text: Well, it sounds like I owe you a drink...

g.title: j3550941996
g.text: Although, maybe now we're even after that drink *you* owe *me.*

g.text: I feel like we'll be discussing this whole Duviri thing again.

g.text: Either way.

g.title: j2563244589
g.text: After whatever nonsense is going on between you and Aoi with some crack about On-lyne?

g.title: j1388115134
g.text: I'm glad you two are making friends, but... either way.
